Deputy President William Ruto and his allies in the united democratic alliance, UDA now say they will not be coerced to leave jubilee party arguing that they are not visitors in the ruling party but founders. While poking holes on the ruling jubilee regime and its leadership, Ruto said they will only leave when it&rsquo;s convenient for them to do so ahead of the 2022 general election. And as Chris Thairu reports, the leaders blamed former NASA principals for the mess the party finds itself in today.
